Canoe Slalom

Arts Documentary hosted by Dougie Vipond and Duncan McCallum and Cameron McNeish and Deziree Wilson, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC The Adventure Show series in 2016 - English narration. 
http://docuwiki.net/images/e/ed/Canoe-Slalom-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------
The Adventure Show takes to the rapids and the stunning white water of the River Tay, near Aberfeldy. We're here for the Grandtully Premier Slalom where Scottish athletes can be guaranteed to do well. This year Olympic gold-medallist, Tim Baillie from Aberdeen, gives an expert's view on the action. Cameron McNeish heads north to meet a remarkable man who, 50 years ago, achieved one of the greatest feats in the history of adventure.
